{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 55c98268-b1ad-459d-851b-25ef52248187\n---\n# Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\nCounter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures  \n  \n## Description  \n This counter is incremented whenever a message is rejected due to a security problem not covered by the \"Security Calls Not Authorized\" counter. Such problems include:  \n  \n-   Client token cannot be read from the message.  \n  \n-   Client token has failed authentication (for example,, bad password).  \n  \n-   Signature verification has failed (for example,, the message has been tampered).  \n  \n-   The message is a duplicate from a previous one, which can happen during a replay attack.  \n  \n-   A decryption failure has occurred.  \n  \n-   Some required elements (for example,, missing timestamp or encrypted data block) are missing from the message.  \n  \n-   Errors have occurred during TLSNEGO/SPNEGO handshake.\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,140],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 55c98268-b1ad-459d-851b-25ef52248187","nodes":[{"content":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"pos":[0,56],"content":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"content":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[0,56]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[147,203],"content":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","linkify":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"content":"Service: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[0,56]}]},{"content":"Counter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[204,265]},{"pos":[274,285],"content":"Description","linkify":"Description","nodes":[{"conten